data.text:
This look at Jason Terry’s 2012-13 season is the fifth in a weekly series analyzing the Nets’ new acquisitions using the NBA.com/Stats database. Slides include “Season at a Glance,” “Soaring Through the Postseason,” “Taking Off in the Third” and “Home Landing.” Notable highlights:

Terry shot .485 on mid-range attempts, 8.4% better than the league average.

“JET” soared in the playoffs for a third straight season, shooting .444 from the field and .441 from long range.

The third quarter proved to be Terry’s best, producing 104.7 points per 100 possessions and a net efficiency rating of +5.0.

Terry played his best in front of the home crowd, stepping up his offense and his defense in Boston.
